'From Squeak3.5alpha of ''7 January 2003'' [latest update: #5173] on 18 March 2003 at 12:27:35 am'!"Change Set:		advanceToBetaOr36-dewDate:			17 March 2003Author:			Doug WayThis is the last update for version 3.5alpha.  In its postscript is an executable statement that will set the version forward either to 3.5beta or to 3.6alpha, at user option"!"Postscript:Offer the chance to advance the version number."(self confirm: 'There are no further updates for Squeak 3.5alpha.Do you wish to advance to version 3.6alpha?[Yes] Your system will be marked as 3.6alpha, and you willsubsequently receive ''test pilot'' updates for 3.6.[No] Your system will be marked as 3.5beta, allowing youto receive only final fixes for the 3.5 release.[Neither] You may choose No, and immediately quit without saving,allowing you to make a backup copy before adopting this change.DO YOU WANT TO ADVANCE to Version 3.6alpha now?')	ifTrue: [SystemVersion newVersion: 'Squeak3.6alpha'.			SystemVersion current date: '17 March 2003'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.6alpha imageand retrieve updates again for 3.6alpha and beyond.']	ifFalse: [SystemVersion current version: 'Squeak3.5beta'; date: '17 March 2003'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.5beta imageand retrieve updates again for any final fixes to 3.5.- - - - -(If you quit without saving now, your image will revert to3.5alpha without any of the updates you just loaded)'].!